Definition: [ἀντιτάσσομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g5021}}; to range oneself against, i.e. oppose
[ἀντίτυπον] neuter of a compound of {{g473}} and {{g5179}}; corresponding ("antitype"), i.e. a representative, counterpart
[ἀντιπαρέρχομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g3928}}; to go along opposite
[Ἀντίπας] contracted for a compound of {{g473}} and a derivative of {{g3962}}; Antipas, a Christian
[Ἀντιόχεια] from Ἀντίοχυς (a Syrian king); Antiochia, a place in Syria
[Ἀντιοχεύς] from {{g490}}; an Antiochian or inhabitant of Antiochia
[ἀντιπίπτω] from {{g473}} and {{g4098}} (including its alternate); to oppose
[ἀντιστρατεύομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g4754}}; (figuratively) to attack, i.e. (by implication) destroy
[Ἀντιπατρίς] from the same as {{g493}}; Antipatris, a place in Palestine
[ἀντιπέραν] from {{g473}} and {{g4008}}; on the opposite side
[ἀνεκλάλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1583}}; not spoken out, i.e. (by implication) unutterable
[ἀνέκλειπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1587}}; not left out, i.e. (by implication) inexhaustible
[ἀνέγκλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1458}}; unaccused, i.e. (by implication) irreproachable
[ἀνεκδιήγητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1555}}; not expounded in full, i.e. indescribable
[ἀνεμίζω] from {{g417}}; to toss with the wind
[ἄνεμος] from the base of {{g109}}; wind; (plural) by implication, (the four) quarters (of the earth)
[ἀνεκτότερος] comparative of a derivative of {{g430}}; more endurable
[ἀνελεήμων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1655}}; merciless
[ἀνένδεκτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as {{g1735}}; unadmitted, i.e. (by implication) not supposable
[ἀνεξερεύνητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1830}}; not searched out, i.e. (by implication) inscrutable
[ἀντιλογία] from a derivative of {{g483}}; dispute, disobedience
[ἀντίληψις] from {{g482}}; relief
[ἀντίλυτρον] from {{g473}} and {{g3083}}; a redemption-price
[ἀντιλοιδορέω] from {{g473}} and {{g3058}}; to rail in reply
[ἀντικρύ] prolonged from {{g473}}; opposite
[ἀντίκειμαι] from {{g473}} and {{g2749}}; to lie opposite, i.e. be adverse (figuratively, repugnant) to
[ἀντιλέγω] from {{g473}} and {{g3004}}; to dispute, refuse
[ἀντιλαμβάνομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g2983}}; to take hold of in turn, i.e. succor; also to participate
[ἀντιμισθία] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g3408}}; requital, correspondence
[ἀντιμετρέω] from {{g473}} and {{g3354}}; to mete in return
[ἀνδροφόνος] from {{g435}} and {{g5408}}; a murderer
[Ἀνδρόνικος] from {{g435}} and {{g3534}}; man of victory; Andronicos, an Israelite
[ἀνδραποδιστής] from a derivative of a compound of {{g435}} and {{g4228}}; an enslaver (as bringing men to his feet)
[ἀναψύχω] from {{g303}} and {{g5594}}; properly, to cool off, i.e. (figuratively) relieve
[ἀνδρίζομαι] middle voice from {{g435}}; to act manly
[Ἀνδρέας] from {{g435}}; manly; Andreas, an Israelite
[ἀνάχυσις] from a comparative of {{g303}} and χέω (to pour); properly, effusion, i.e. (figuratively) license
[ἀνάψυξις] from {{g404}}; properly, a recovery of breath, i.e. (figuratively) revival
[ἀναχωρέω] from {{g303}} and {{g5562}}; to retire
[ἀντικαθίστημι] from {{g473}} and {{g2525}}; to set down (troops) against, i.e. withstand
[ἀντικαλέω] from {{g473}} and {{g2564}}; to invite in return
[ἀνταποκρίνομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g611}}; to contradict or dispute
[ἀντέπω] from {{g473}} and {{g2036}}; to refute or deny
[ἀντέχομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g2192}}; to hold oneself opposite to, i.e. (by implication) adhere to; by extension to care for
[ἀντί] a primary particle; opposite, i.e. instead or because of (rarely in addition to) Often used in composition to denote contrast, requital, substitution, correspondence, etc.
[ἀντιβάλλω] from {{g473}} and {{g906}}; to bandy
[ἀντιδιατίθεμαι] from {{g473}} and {{g1303}}; to set oneself opposite, i.e. be  disputatious
[ἀντίδικος] from {{g473}} and {{g1349}}; an opponent (in a lawsuit); specially, Satan (as the arch-enemy)
[ἀντίθεσις] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g5087}}; opposition, i.e. a conflict (of theories)
[ἀνταπόδοσις] from {{g467}}; requital (properly, the act)
[ἀνταπόδομα] from {{g467}}; a requital (properly, the thing)
[ἀντίχριστος] from {{g473}} and {{g5547}}; an opponent of the Messiah
[ἀνοχή] from {{g430}}; self-restraint, i.e. tolerance
[ἀνόσιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3741}}; wicked
[ἀνορθόω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of the base of {{g3717}}; to straighten up
[ἀνόμως] adverb from {{g459}}; lawlessly, i.e. (specially) not amenable to (the Jewish) law
[ἀνταποδίδωμι] from {{g473}} and {{g591}}; to requite (good or evil)
[ἀνταναπληρόω] from {{g473}} and {{g378}}; to supplement
[ἀντάλλαγμα] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g236}}; an equivalent or ransom
[ἀνταγωνίζομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g75}}; to struggle against (figuratively) ("antagonize")
[ἀνοικοδομέω] from {{g303}} and {{g3618}}; to rebuild
[ἄνοιξις] from {{g455}}; opening (throat)
[ἄνοια] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3563}}; stupidity; by implication, rage
[ἀνοίγω] from {{g303}} and οἴγω (to open); to open up (literally or figuratively, in various applications)
[Ἄννας] of Hebrew origin ({{h2608}}); Annas (i.e. {{g367}}), an Israelite
[ἀνόητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3539}}; unintelligent; by implication, sensual
[ἀνίστημι] from {{g303}} and {{g2476}}; to stand up (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive)
[Ἄννα] of Hebrew origin ({{h2584}}); Anna, an Israelitess
[ἀνομία] from {{g459}}; illegality, i.e. violation of law or (genitive case) wickedness
[ἄνομος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3551}}; lawless, i.e. (negatively) not subject to (the Jewish) law; (by implication, a Gentile), or (positively) wicked
[ἀνθρωπάρεσκος] from {{g444}} and {{g700}}; man-courting, i.e. fawning
[ἄνθραξ] of uncertain derivation; a live coal
[ἀνθρωποκτόνος] from {{g444}} and κτείνω(to kill); a manslayer Compare {{g5406}}.
[ἀνθρώπινος] from {{g444}}; human
[ἀνθυπατεύω] from {{g446}}; to act as proconsul
[ἄνθρωπος] from {{g435}} and ὤψ (the countenance; from {{g3700}}); man-faced, i.e. a human being
[ἀνίημι] from {{g303}} and ἵημι (to send); to let up, i.e. (literally) slacken or (figuratively) desert, desist from
[ἀνθύπατος] from {{g473}} and a superlative of {{g5228}}; instead of the highest officer, i.e. (specially) a Roman proconsul
[ἄνιπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3538}}; without ablution
[ἀνίλεως] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2436}}; inexorable
[ἀνήμερος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and ἥμερος (lame); savage
[ἀνήρ] a primary word (compare {{g444}}); a man (properly as an individual male)
[ἀνθίστημι] from {{g473}} and {{g2476}}; to stand against, i.e. oppose
[ἀνθομολογέομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g3670}}; to confess in turn, i.e. respond in praise
[ἀνέχομαι] middle voice from {{g303}} and {{g2192}}; to hold oneself up against, i.e. (figuratively) put up with
[ἀνεψιός] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and an obsolete νέπος (a brood); properly, akin, i.e. (specially) a cousin
[ἄνηθον] probably of foreign origin; dill
[ἀνήκω] from {{g303}} and {{g2240}}; to attain to, i.e. (figuratively) be proper
[ἄνθος] a primary word; a blossom
[ἀνθρακιά] from {{g440}}; a bed of burning coals
[ἄνευ] a primary particle; without Compare {{g1}}.
[ἀνετάζω] from {{g303}} and ἐτάζω (to test); to investigate (judicially)
[ἄνεσις] from {{g447}}; relaxation or (figuratively) relief
[ἀνέρχομαι] from {{g303}} and {{g2064}}; to ascend
[ἀνεπίληπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1949}}; not arrested, i.e. (by implication) inculpable
[ἀνεπαίσχυντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{g1909}} and {{g153}}; not ashamed, i.e. irreprehensible:
[ἀνεξιχνίαστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g2487}}; not tracked out, i.e. (by implication) untraceable
[ἀνεξίκακος] from {{g430}} and {{g2556}}; enduring of ill, i.e. forbearing
[ἀνευρίσκω] from {{g303}} and {{g2147}}; to find out
[ἀνεύθετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2111}}; not well set, i.e. inconvenient
